nodes.title: Note: Saving frames
widgets_values:
* To save all frames of your base video as png images: Activate the 'Save Frame (Base)' node (CTRL+B) on the right.

* Images will be saved in the [Project Path]/frames_base/[Movie Name] folder (configurable below).

Warning: Images are never erased or overwritten, and will be saved each time you run a new batch. Once your frames are saved, it's highly recommended to deactivate the node.
Bypass (CTRL+B) the 'ControlNet Preview Image' node on top to also disable this group.

Same as for the Upscaler, run this in solo only.
Building a long final movie, especially if you have a lot of intermediate frames (multiplier field), ask a lot of ram.

To avoid wasting precious RAM and to be able to process numerous frames, this Hires Video group is working as a standalone pass:
A generic Hires fix upscale is done here by using as input png frames from your last base video rendering.
This way, the video input, ControlNet stack and Animated diff pass are not loaded anymore, we just run an upscale.
